SOCIAL media is helping the general public aid police in solving crimes, according to a charity. Online sleuths help Scots cops crack cases SOCIAL media is helping the general public aid police in solving crimes, according to a charity.Crimestoppers Scotland, in its annual report, said it took more than a third of a million calls from members of the public.A similar number of tip-offs were made in online forms, enabling the charity to pass on 101,103 pieces of information to police, leading to 7119 criminals arrested and charged.Angela Parker, regional manager for Crimestoppers in Scotland, said: &quot;Crimestoppers' campaigns have made a measurable difference at a local level as well as Scotland-wide and we would like to thank the Scottish public in helping our fight against crime.&quot; 